Overall, PCoA combined with ANOSIM showed a statistically significant separation between samples obtained from freshwater and saline sites for both skin microbiomes (
  p < 0.001; 
  Figure 3A), and intestinal microbiomes (
  p < 0.001; 
  Figure 3B). This indicates that salinity is a primary factor in defining these microbial communities. For the 60 skin and intestinal microbiome samples used for within-fish comparisons where possible, ANOSIM showed that the communities obtained from the two sample types were significantly different (
  p < 0.001; 
  Figure 4).
